'Grampus' may refer to: *A common name historically used for the orca
*''Grampus'' (genus), the genus that includes Risso's dolphin as its only
species *CSS ''Grampus'', a Confederate river steamer *USS Grampus, the name of
a number of ships of the United States Navy *HMS Grampus, the name of a number
of Royal Navy ships and submarines *the Grampus class submarines, built in the
style of HMS ''Grampus'' <!--*Grampus Heritage and Training, Ltd., an
archaeology and traditional skills organization in northern England--> *Grampus
(TUGS) a character from the children's series TUGS *Nagoya Grampus, a Japanese
soccer club <!--*Grampus (RR), a small 4 wheel railroad flatcar--> *A versatile
attack, reconnaissance and research sub used by the Blue Fleet in the anime
series [[Blue Submarine No. 6]] *Another name for the hellbender salamander
